      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the two theories thing, but isn't there a difference in terms of legal rigor? like, can't you say that originalism is more \"accurate\" because it stays closer to the actual text, whereas \"living constitutionalism\" is just a way for judges to push their own political agendas? it feels like one is based on facts and the other is just... making it up as they go.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
